1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:03,110
(theme song)

2
00:00:03,110 --> 00:01:44,280
♪

3
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:49,160
(maniacal laughter)

4
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:56,000
♪

5
00:01:58,080 --> 00:02:00,050
(chanting)

6
00:02:01,130 --> 00:02:03,050
Jinpu!

7
00:02:03,050 --> 00:02:04,250
(zapping)

8
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:06,220
You can't fight Tang shui.

9
00:02:08,180 --> 00:02:09,280
Ha!

10
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:11,270
I need to see the Commander.

11
00:02:11,270 --> 00:02:14,190
Hey, who's out there?

12
00:02:14,190 --> 00:02:17,040
Please listen.

13
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:19,250
Kanaji's shrine was
a principal point of ki

14
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:22,020
that was built to
protect the city of Edo.

15
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:24,130
When it burned down
during the the Uno War,

16
00:02:24,130 --> 00:02:27,060
the flow of ki was
weakened considerably.

17
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:29,230
The shrine was designed
in a dragon formation,

18
00:02:29,230 --> 00:02:32,140
with the head being
the grave of Tokugawa's.

19
00:02:32,140 --> 00:02:34,180
It was located at
the northeastern section

20
00:02:34,180 --> 00:02:35,260
of the shrine.

21
00:02:35,260 --> 00:02:37,100
Its unfortunate destruction

22
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:39,210
made it impossible
to restore the formation

23
00:02:39,210 --> 00:02:41,120
to its original power.

24
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:43,040
We've tried to do
the best we could,

25
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:45,280
but it has never been
the same as before.

26
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:48,040
We've used sand
to simulate water.

27
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:50,220
It hasn't been as effective
as the actual spring

28
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:52,210
located at
the throat of the dragon.

29
00:02:52,210 --> 00:02:55,280
We hope this will quench
the dragon's thirst.

30
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:57,250
You're finished with most of it.

31
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,250
What more needs to
be done, old man?

32
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:01,280
You've given the dragon
a head, a throat,

33
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,250
and four limbs.

34
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:03,270
It's complete.

35
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:05,080
No, it's not.

36
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:07,240
It doesn't have a heart.

37
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,270
(grunting)

38
00:03:08,270 --> 00:03:10,240
I don't think this door's
been opened for years.

39
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:12,090
♪

40
00:03:12,090 --> 00:03:14,070
Oh, it smells musty.

41
00:03:14,070 --> 00:03:15,130
Ugh!

42
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:16,180
What's that?

43
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:17,280
It's a dragon sculpture.

44
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:20,010
-It used to be in the spring.
-Ugh!

45
00:03:20,010 --> 00:03:22,230
The Master Jingoro
Hidari created it.

46
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:24,230
We can use it to
complete the formation.

47
00:03:24,230 --> 00:03:27,160
It will be a good
substitute for the heart.

48
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:30,250
♪

49
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:42,130
(chanting)

50
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:53,100
♪

51
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:54,230
You're late coming.

52
00:03:54,230 --> 00:03:57,170
I came as soon as I was able.

53
00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:58,140
There's not much time

54
00:03:58,140 --> 00:04:00,200
before the ki passes
through this place.

55
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:06,130
♪

56
00:04:06,130 --> 00:04:07,220
This is weird.

57
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:09,030
Tang shui.

58
00:04:09,030 --> 00:04:10,200
We've found Reisui.

59
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:22,140
♪

60
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:24,270
They appear to be sitting
in some kind of vigil.

61
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:26,040
They're combining their powers

62
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,270
to make the ki change direction.

63
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:29,100
To accomplish that
they must control

64
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,000
the five point star
that's centered

65
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,280
on the Chuzenji lake bed.

66
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:35,070
If we manage to
destroy their strategy

67
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:37,040
and put a stop to
their evil plan,

68
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:39,270
what will happen to the ki
that's coming this way?

69
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:41,180
The ground in Nikko's purified.

70
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:43,170
If the ki reaches there,
it will be cleansed

71
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:45,100
and eventually lose
much of its power.

72
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:47,250
After a while it
will simply go away.

73
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:49,200
♪

74
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:52,040
(panting)

75
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:54,040
Huh?

76
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:56,010
I can hardly believe
they found us.

77
00:04:56,010 --> 00:04:58,270
Just what should we do now?

78
00:04:58,270 --> 00:05:01,060
Did you hear
what I just said?

79
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:02,020
Hey, wait!

80
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:03,150
What is that?

81
00:05:03,150 --> 00:05:04,230
It's Tang shui.

82
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:06,021
(speaking foreign phrase)

83
00:05:06,021 --> 00:05:07,260
What? Not that!

84
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:08,260
Ah!

85
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:14,070
Ah!

86
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:15,040
(grunting)

87
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:21,010
(shouting)

88
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:30,040
They all disappeared.

89
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,270
What happened to my jinmen?

90
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:33,010
Don't worry, Saeki.

91
00:05:33,010 --> 00:05:34,290
They became one
with the flames.

92
00:05:34,290 --> 00:05:37,000
That's the way
they wanted it to be.

93
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,030
Reisui, you're insane!

94
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:42,080
Let's go through!

95
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:42,941
Mm-hm.

96
00:05:42,941 --> 00:05:44,100
Don't move.

97
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:46,010
You have to be
trained in feng shui

98
00:05:46,010 --> 00:05:48,010
to be able to attempt it.

99
00:05:48,010 --> 00:05:49,170
I'll try.

100
00:05:49,170 --> 00:05:51,280
The real battle
is about to begin.

101
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:53,270
Don't, Jinpu.

102
00:05:53,270 --> 00:05:55,240
If I don't come back,

103
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:58,140
promise me you'll
take care of everything.

104
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:00,160
Huh--Jinpu, here?

105
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,240
(zapping)

106
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,240
(grunting)

107
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,160
♪

108
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,040
Over here!

109
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,070
Watch the head!

110
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:09,270
♪

111
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:11,280
It wasn't easy hauling
that monstrosity.

112
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,240
Good work, men.

113
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,250
It's not great,

114
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:16,040
but at least we did our best.

115
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:18,060
Yes.

116
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:19,160
Will it work?

117
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:22,210
Yes, but I cannot predict
how effective it will be.

118
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:24,280
If it only gives off some power,

119
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:27,230
it'll be better than
having nothing there at all.

120
00:06:27,230 --> 00:06:30,200
We'll have to rely
on Jinpu to help us.

121
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,110
Let's go.

122
00:06:31,110 --> 00:06:32,210
The Senate House.

123
00:06:32,210 --> 00:06:34,130
Why should we save those rats?

124
00:06:34,130 --> 00:06:35,240
Even though many
of our officials

125
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:37,030
have been accused of bribery,

126
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,220
we can't allow
them to be killed.

127
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:39,240
You're right.

128
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:43,070
♪

129
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:45,040
(soft rumbling)

130
00:06:51,110 --> 00:06:52,220
He's here!

131
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:54,200
Huh?

132
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:56,110
Jinpu, you need to understand

133
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:57,230
why I've come back.

134
00:06:59,090 --> 00:07:01,140
My family had to go through
such unbearable pain

135
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:02,280
when they left for China.

136
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:05,230
Many died knowing
terrible suffering.

137
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:09,020
We have both endured
our share of losses, Reisui.

138
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:11,080
But our families shouldn't
continue to hate each other

139
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:12,260
for the sins of the past.

140
00:07:12,260 --> 00:07:14,200
I want some revenge.

141
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,010
That won't help any of us.

142
00:07:16,010 --> 00:07:18,000
We must end this
shameful squabble.

143
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:20,230
We should make amends for the
good of our country at least.

144
00:07:20,230 --> 00:07:21,190
Never!

145
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:22,160
Die!

146
00:07:24,090 --> 00:07:25,060
(grunts)

147
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:29,270
(grunting)

148
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:31,240
(otherworldly sounds)

149
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,260
(rumbling)

150
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,010
You seem edgy.

151
00:07:52,010 --> 00:07:53,230
Those big shots
we're trying to save

152
00:07:53,230 --> 00:07:55,100
are corrupt and despicable.

153
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,050
I know they are.

154
00:07:56,050 --> 00:07:57,080
I've investigated them.

155
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:58,090
So what?

156
00:07:58,090 --> 00:07:59,270
Why should we waste
all of our energy

157
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:01,020
trying to help them?

158
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:03,200
They're nothing but a bunch
of deceitful criminals.

159
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,140
♪

160
00:08:05,140 --> 00:08:06,160
(grunts)

161
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,150
I'm still obligated to them.

162
00:08:08,150 --> 00:08:09,110
They're human beings.

163
00:08:09,110 --> 00:08:10,250
That's all that matters.

164
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:13,050
My job as a policeman
is to protect and serve

165
00:08:13,050 --> 00:08:14,080
the community.

166
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:16,200
My personal feelings
can't interfere with my job.

167
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,050
I made a promise
to uphold this creed

168
00:08:18,050 --> 00:08:19,140
and I will honor it.

169
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:20,120
Hm.

170
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,170
I'll buy that.

171
00:08:21,170 --> 00:08:23,090
I might have a plan
that will help you.

172
00:08:23,090 --> 00:08:24,100
Would you like to hear it?

173
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,160
Well, I'm open to anything.

174
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:27,020
What is it?

175
00:08:27,020 --> 00:08:28,160
Those officials are scum,

176
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:32,020
but I suppose Kawaji is
doing the honorable thing.

177
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:34,090
(grunting)

178
00:08:34,090 --> 00:08:36,110
His power is equal to mine.

179
00:08:36,110 --> 00:08:37,290
One of us will have
to give up his life

180
00:08:37,290 --> 00:08:39,240
to succeed at this game.

181
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,160
I am not letting go.

182
00:08:41,160 --> 00:08:43,210
I have to win.

183
00:08:43,210 --> 00:08:45,160
(screaming)

184
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,240
Don't do it, Jinpu.

185
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,150
You're going to kill us all.

186
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:52,210
♪

187
00:08:52,210 --> 00:08:53,240
Reisui, do something.

188
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,050
You've got to stop him.

189
00:08:55,050 --> 00:08:56,150
♪

190
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:58,210
I won't allow you to
interfere with our dreams

191
00:08:58,210 --> 00:09:00,130
to dominate this country.

192
00:09:00,130 --> 00:09:02,230
♪

193
00:09:02,230 --> 00:09:04,010
Do you hear?

194
00:09:04,010 --> 00:09:05,100
♪

195
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:07,210
(shouting foreign phrase)

196
00:09:07,210 --> 00:09:10,130
♪

197
00:09:10,130 --> 00:09:11,052
Huh?

198
00:09:11,052 --> 00:09:12,140
What's he doing?

199
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:14,120
♪

200
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:16,130
Ah!

201
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:22,020
♪

202
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:23,200
Don't be stupid, Jinpu.

203
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,120
The power of feng
shui will be lost

204
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,200
and disappear forever!

205
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:30,210
If the destruction of feng shui
is the will of Heaven and Earth,

206
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:33,110
then we must accept our fate.

207
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:49,000
♪

208
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,220
Hey, he's gone.

209
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:55,260
♪

210
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:57,260
(grunting)

211
00:09:57,260 --> 00:10:01,260
♪

212
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,180
Oh...

213
00:10:02,180 --> 00:10:04,060
Jinpu, are you all right?

214
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:10,000
Our fate was determined

215
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,220
the day the wind
and water families fought.

216
00:10:12,220 --> 00:10:14,100
Did we get them, Kenshin?

217
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:15,140
I'm not really sure,

218
00:10:15,140 --> 00:10:17,893
but you certainly gave them
something to think about.

219
00:10:17,893 --> 00:10:18,652
Huh?

220
00:10:18,652 --> 00:10:20,090
What's that, hm?

221
00:10:25,090 --> 00:10:26,220
Reisui.

222
00:10:29,010 --> 00:10:31,070
♪

223
00:10:31,070 --> 00:10:33,220
The man who is willing
to make the eternal sacrifice

224
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:36,290
will be the ultimate
winner in this battle.

225
00:10:36,290 --> 00:10:39,090
Water will reign
over this country.

226
00:10:39,090 --> 00:10:41,110
That's what we've always wanted.

227
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:44,000
Our dream will live.

228
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,260
It just won't work.

229
00:10:45,260 --> 00:10:47,190
(grunting)

230
00:10:47,190 --> 00:10:48,230
♪

231
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:49,260
Don't do it.

232
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:51,170
It's coming back!

233
00:10:51,170 --> 00:10:53,220
They must have
rebuilt their jin.

234
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:58,270
♪

235
00:10:58,270 --> 00:10:59,270
(gasping)

236
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:02,210
♪

237
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:04,060
What is that?

238
00:11:04,060 --> 00:11:06,110
I have waited for this day.

239
00:11:06,110 --> 00:11:07,210
My time has come.

240
00:11:07,210 --> 00:11:08,260
I won't die.

241
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:11,090
My legacy will keep
my memory alive forever.

242
00:11:11,090 --> 00:11:12,130
(grunting)

243
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:14,000
Our side will win!

244
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,010
(grunting)

245
00:11:15,010 --> 00:11:18,030
Then my family will
become the rulers of Japan!

246
00:11:18,030 --> 00:11:20,160
I shall fulfill that promise!

247
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:23,200
We could have lived
together like brothers.

248
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,100
We are feng shui.

249
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:27,030
Now it'll disappear forever.

250
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:29,030
(screaming)

251
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:32,150
♪

252
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,290
As head of the water family,

253
00:11:33,290 --> 00:11:36,110
Reisui dedicated
himself to his mission.

254
00:11:36,110 --> 00:11:40,000
His final act will assure
our family victory over wind.

255
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,220
Saeki.

256
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:43,090
(grunting)

257
00:11:43,090 --> 00:11:44,090
♪

258
00:11:44,090 --> 00:11:46,040
Reisui was determined
to bring honor

259
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,010
back to the water family's name.

260
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:49,270
He succeeded by
rebuilding the jin

261
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:52,200
and taking control of the ki.

262
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,040
The ki's coming.

263
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,160
It'll be here very soon.

264
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:57,160
(rumbling)

265
00:11:57,160 --> 00:12:14,240
♪

266
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:15,190
Oh no.

267
00:12:15,190 --> 00:12:17,120
We need to stop it.

268
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:18,180
Ask him.

269
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:20,050
♪

270
00:12:20,050 --> 00:12:21,120
Let's talk.

271
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,120
♪

272
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:24,040
What do you want?

273
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:27,100
Give me the real
gold heralding device.

274
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:28,160
That's right.

275
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,230
♪

276
00:12:29,230 --> 00:12:31,070
(trembling)

277
00:12:31,070 --> 00:12:32,040
♪

278
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:36,200
Sir Horobi Hitu
has just arrived.

279
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:39,040
Please make way
for Sir Yamahuchi.

280
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,250
The police want us to leave.

281
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,110
That's absolutely preposterous.

282
00:12:42,110 --> 00:12:43,170
Whatever for?

283
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:45,200
Some sort of security problem.

284
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,290
They won't say what it is.

285
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:50,010
They're being completely
unreasonable if you ask me.

286
00:12:50,010 --> 00:12:52,270
Excuse me, but I must
ask you to leave, sir.

287
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:54,290
We can't put their
lives in danger.

288
00:12:54,290 --> 00:12:56,090
This is an important meeting.

289
00:12:56,090 --> 00:12:59,130
We can't cancel it unless
we have a specific reason.

290
00:12:59,130 --> 00:13:00,090
Come on, Chief.

291
00:13:00,090 --> 00:13:01,030
Hm?

292
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,160
Let's go.

293
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,180
A gold heralding device?

294
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:10,000
♪

295
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,130
What in the world is that?

296
00:13:11,130 --> 00:13:13,090
You know it.

297
00:13:13,090 --> 00:13:15,090
That man stinks
more than a skunk.

298
00:13:15,090 --> 00:13:16,070
(growls)

299
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:17,180
You weasel!

300
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:18,290
I want it!

301
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:20,010
(grunts)

302
00:13:20,010 --> 00:13:21,100
♪

303
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,010
Ah, ah!

304
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:24,100
Watch out, Sano!

305
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:28,210
♪

306
00:13:28,210 --> 00:13:30,180
(screaming)

307
00:13:33,010 --> 00:13:41,120
♪

308
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:43,140
The ground.

309
00:13:43,140 --> 00:13:44,170
It's gone.

310
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:46,190
How the hell did he do that?

311
00:13:46,190 --> 00:13:47,280
It's actually true.

312
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:50,160
Saeki does have
the gold heralding device.

313
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:52,280
It's crazy to let
that lunatic keep it.

314
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:55,230
(evil laughter)

315
00:13:55,230 --> 00:13:57,030
Yes, I have it,

316
00:13:57,030 --> 00:13:58,220
and I'm never
going to let it go,

317
00:13:58,220 --> 00:14:00,160
so don't make any
attempt to retrieve it

318
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:02,270
or I'll wipe you off
the face of the earth.

319
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:04,240
With this heralding device,

320
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:07,230
I won't need Reisui to help
me take over the government.

321
00:14:07,230 --> 00:14:10,080
Saeki found out about
the gold heralding device

322
00:14:10,080 --> 00:14:13,030
from the decree that separated
Buddhism from Shintoism.

323
00:14:13,030 --> 00:14:15,290
Then I bet he must have
stolen it from the Yome Gate.

324
00:14:15,290 --> 00:14:17,280
He probably kept it
hidden from Reisui

325
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:19,180
so he wouldn't find out.

326
00:14:19,180 --> 00:14:21,070
It cost Reisui his life.

327
00:14:21,070 --> 00:14:22,060
If he'd know about it,

328
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:23,290
he wouldn't have had
to sacrifice himself.

329
00:14:23,290 --> 00:14:26,010
Saeki planned that all along.

330
00:14:26,010 --> 00:14:28,050
He was holding it in
his hand and watched

331
00:14:28,050 --> 00:14:29,290
as Reisui died a horrible death

332
00:14:29,290 --> 00:14:32,010
that had no meaning whatsoever,

333
00:14:32,010 --> 00:14:34,150
and it was because he wanted
to control this country

334
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:37,010
without any interference
from the water family.

335
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:39,100
It's too late to stop the ki
from heading into the city,

336
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:42,100
but we may be able to prevent it
from causing mass destruction.

337
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:43,220
It's traveling at a rapid rate,

338
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:45,090
so we have to act fast.

339
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:47,190
First, we must destroy
the stone monument.

340
00:14:47,190 --> 00:14:49,110
Then if we get
a hold of that device,

341
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:52,050
we can change
the direction of the ki.

342
00:14:52,050 --> 00:14:54,160
Let's just hope I'm right.

343
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:55,160
Kenshin, no.

344
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,240
There's no time to contemplate.

345
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:58,170
Come on, Sanosuke, let's go!

346
00:14:58,170 --> 00:14:59,240
All right.

347
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:01,100
(panting)

348
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,070
(ticking)

349
00:15:05,010 --> 00:15:06,070
(explosion)

350
00:15:06,070 --> 00:15:07,140
-Was that a cannon?
-What's going on?

351
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:09,290
(rumbling)
(explosion)

352
00:15:09,290 --> 00:15:11,260
(shouting)

353
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:17,290
Well, can't say we
didn't warn 'em, huh?

354
00:15:17,290 --> 00:15:19,110
Get out of the building!

355
00:15:19,110 --> 00:15:20,210
Explosion!

356
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:22,120
Whoa, hey, you big buffoons!

357
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:24,120
One of you at
a time, come on now!

358
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:28,140
(panting)

359
00:15:28,140 --> 00:15:30,290
You have to face reality,
Battousai the Slasher.

360
00:15:30,290 --> 00:15:32,230
Both you and that
feng shui reprobate

361
00:15:32,230 --> 00:15:35,140
are just worthless
has-beens of the past.

362
00:15:35,140 --> 00:15:37,260
I will be a new
light from now on,

363
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:39,250
the light of
a shining new empire.

364
00:15:42,250 --> 00:15:45,140
(grunting)

365
00:15:45,140 --> 00:15:46,100
(shouting)

366
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,100
Get out!

367
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:48,070
Quickly!

368
00:15:48,070 --> 00:15:50,040
(panting)

369
00:15:51,110 --> 00:15:52,270
Relax, it's over.

370
00:15:55,030 --> 00:15:57,060
Is there anybody
that hasn't gotten out?

371
00:15:57,060 --> 00:15:58,140
We're the only ones left.

372
00:15:58,140 --> 00:15:59,120
I checked.

373
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:01,040
Everyone got out safely.

374
00:16:01,040 --> 00:16:02,030
That's good.

375
00:16:02,030 --> 00:16:04,090
The evacuation has
now been completed, sir.

376
00:16:04,090 --> 00:16:05,100
Hm?

377
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:07,070
It all came off amazingly well.

378
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:10,000
If those big shots only knew
how much danger they'd been in,

379
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,080
they would have dragged me
through the mud for sure.

380
00:16:14,150 --> 00:16:15,120
Huh?

381
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,180
It's up to us now.

382
00:16:18,180 --> 00:16:19,240
Do or die.

383
00:16:22,210 --> 00:16:23,170
Do you hear that?

384
00:16:23,170 --> 00:16:25,150
Out of the way, coming through!

385
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:27,290
Did you make sure the area's
been secured in Kanaji?

386
00:16:27,290 --> 00:16:29,080
Yes, it is secured, sir.

387
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,270
Good, we have to get
over there right away

388
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:33,080
and see if the ki has
caused any further destruction.

389
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:35,080
We've done
everything we can so far.

390
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:37,000
Let's just hope that
our jin will hold up

391
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,280
and protect the city from harm.

392
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:41,090
Heralding device,
shield this stone monument

393
00:16:41,090 --> 00:16:43,010
and don't let it be destroyed.

394
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:45,210
You are the bastion of my power.

395
00:16:45,210 --> 00:16:47,150
I'll rule all Japan!

396
00:16:47,150 --> 00:16:49,250
(rumbling)

397
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:50,220
Ah!

398
00:16:53,130 --> 00:16:55,290
(screaming)

399
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:57,250
A new day will dawn.

400
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:59,240
The future of Japan
is in my hands,

401
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,250
and nobody can
take it away from me.

402
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:03,290
Now I'll be able
to manipulate the ki

403
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:06,110
and change the entire
structure of the government.

404
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:08,190
The masses will be
forced to follow my will.

405
00:17:08,190 --> 00:17:09,270
I'm in control.

406
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:12,140
The light of world shines on me!

407
00:17:12,140 --> 00:17:13,280
No matter what he's thinking,

408
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,200
he's only a human being.

409
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,040
Light cannot shine on a man

410
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,280
who is possessed by evil.

411
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:20,190
Spirits of Heaven and Earth,

412
00:17:20,190 --> 00:17:22,120
please protect us.

413
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:25,040
♪

414
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:26,090
Now!

415
00:17:26,090 --> 00:17:27,130
Ah!

416
00:17:27,130 --> 00:17:28,130
♪

417
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:30,070
Yah!

418
00:17:30,070 --> 00:17:37,050
♪

419
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:39,030
It's the force of the spiral!

420
00:17:39,030 --> 00:17:41,150
♪

421
00:17:41,150 --> 00:17:44,040
(screaming)

422
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,130
♪

423
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:47,090
Jinpu,

424
00:17:47,090 --> 00:17:48,130
catch!

425
00:17:48,130 --> 00:17:50,180
♪

426
00:17:50,180 --> 00:17:52,150
I got it.

427
00:17:52,150 --> 00:17:53,280
No, Jinpu!

428
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:55,080
(grunting)

429
00:17:55,080 --> 00:17:57,040
I'm going to send
the ki to the southeast

430
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:58,120
so it can dissipate.

431
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:00,050
Hurry, move out of the way!

432
00:18:00,050 --> 00:18:08,260
♪

433
00:18:08,260 --> 00:18:10,260
(indistinct shouting)

434
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:23,130
♪

435
00:18:26,257 --> 00:18:27,270
(explosion)

436
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:35,040
(indistinct shouting)

437
00:18:35,040 --> 00:18:36,140
They did it.

438
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:41,190
No, for now it is
moving this way.

439
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:42,290
It might hit us!

440
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,050
There's just no
way we can stop it.

441
00:18:50,050 --> 00:18:52,110
Oh!

442
00:18:52,110 --> 00:18:54,080
(rumbling)

443
00:19:03,070 --> 00:19:05,040
(otherworldly howl)

444
00:19:11,130 --> 00:19:12,100
(otherworldly shriek)

445
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,290
It stopped itself.

446
00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:22,090
Somehow it just
fizzled right out.

447
00:19:22,090 --> 00:19:23,130
They must have done it.

448
00:19:23,130 --> 00:19:25,210
Yes, I believe they did.

449
00:19:25,210 --> 00:19:27,220
Uh, Mr. Kawaji?

450
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:28,230
What is it?

451
00:19:28,230 --> 00:19:30,200
It looks like
Tsunan's disappeared.

452
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:31,250
♪

453
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:34,050
I know where he's gone.

454
00:19:34,050 --> 00:19:36,160
I bet he's gone back
to the Senate House.

455
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:38,290
He does have a nose
for controversy.

456
00:19:38,290 --> 00:19:42,290
♪

457
00:19:42,290 --> 00:19:45,000
The light...

458
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,170
has gone out.

459
00:19:46,170 --> 00:19:54,130
♪

460
00:19:54,130 --> 00:19:57,230
Jinpu, you did
an excellent job, my son.

461
00:19:57,230 --> 00:20:00,090
But I couldn't have
done it without your help.

462
00:20:00,090 --> 00:20:03,060
You gave us the answers
we needed to defeat Saeki.

463
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:04,200
The man was insane.

464
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:06,170
It was all I could do
to protect the city

465
00:20:06,170 --> 00:20:08,240
from the evil influences
he would have brought.

466
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:10,030
♪

467
00:20:10,030 --> 00:20:12,240
This is too powerful
for ordinary humans.

468
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:16,030
We should throw it down to
the bottom of Musashino Spring.

469
00:20:16,030 --> 00:20:18,030
I will. I give you my promise.

470
00:20:18,030 --> 00:20:19,260
Take care of our country, Jinpu.

471
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:22,250
Keep it safe and prosperous
for as long as you live.

472
00:20:22,250 --> 00:20:23,280
Yes, sir.

473
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:25,060
Goodbye, Horita.

474
00:20:25,060 --> 00:20:27,020
♪

475
00:20:27,020 --> 00:20:28,090
(indistinct shouting)

476
00:20:28,090 --> 00:20:30,150
The building will be as
good as new in no time, sir.

477
00:20:30,150 --> 00:20:34,000
♪

478
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:36,060
You want to know the
real story, Sano?

479
00:20:36,060 --> 00:20:38,230
The old man was once
the commissioner of the shrine.

480
00:20:38,230 --> 00:20:41,000
His full name is
Horita Masamutsu.

481
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,160
Commissioner of the shrine?

482
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:43,190
That explains it.

483
00:20:43,190 --> 00:20:45,110
Tell me, Tsunan,
how come you didn't mention

484
00:20:45,110 --> 00:20:47,070
anything about this
in your article?

485
00:20:47,070 --> 00:20:48,130
I couldn't.

486
00:20:48,130 --> 00:20:50,200
I know, you made the article
about the corrupted officials

487
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,170
so big there wasn't space.

488
00:20:52,170 --> 00:20:54,190
Papers need a little
scandal to sell.

489
00:20:54,190 --> 00:20:56,090
Besides, Saeki
immediately confessed

490
00:20:56,090 --> 00:20:57,190
to bribing all those men.

491
00:20:57,190 --> 00:21:00,060
I was pretty impressed
with Kawaji's determination.

492
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:01,100
Well, that's a surprise.

493
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:02,230
I never thought
you'd say anything nice

494
00:21:02,230 --> 00:21:04,020
about the police department.

495
00:21:04,020 --> 00:21:05,140
Hm?

496
00:21:05,140 --> 00:21:07,240
Hey Yoshi, quit being so lazy.

497
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:09,090
I need some help
with this laundry,

498
00:21:09,090 --> 00:21:10,290
so you get off your butt.

499
00:21:10,290 --> 00:21:11,912
It's just not fair.

500
00:21:11,912 --> 00:21:12,753
Why me?

501
00:21:12,753 --> 00:21:14,170
'Cause I'm the boss.

502
00:21:14,170 --> 00:21:16,090
All right, all right!

503
00:21:16,090 --> 00:21:17,090
♪

504
00:21:17,090 --> 00:21:18,060
Ready?

505
00:21:18,060 --> 00:21:19,030
Let's go.

506
00:21:20,060 --> 00:21:25,290
♪

507
00:21:25,290 --> 00:21:27,050
Hm?

508
00:21:27,050 --> 00:21:28,050
♪

509
00:21:28,050 --> 00:21:29,170
I'm sorry, Kenshin.

510
00:21:29,170 --> 00:21:31,120
I would have liked
to have known you better.

511
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:33,020
I must move on.

512
00:21:33,020 --> 00:21:35,270
I know.
We appreciate all
of your help, Jinpu.

513
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:38,020
Good luck in all your travels.

514
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:40,080
Well, I couldn't have done
it without you and Sano.

515
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:43,170
And I do hope that you're never
burdened with another problem.

516
00:21:43,170 --> 00:21:46,190
Kenshin, I'm very glad
to have known you,

517
00:21:46,190 --> 00:21:48,160
and I hope you have a good life.

518
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:50,040
I'm sure you will.

519
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:52,080
And you will, too.

520
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:54,040
Samurai and feng shui experts

521
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:56,030
may be out of style
in this new age,

522
00:21:56,030 --> 00:21:57,240
but at least we're not lonely.

523
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:59,220
It's important that
we direct our energies

524
00:21:59,220 --> 00:22:01,110
in a positive direction.

525
00:22:01,110 --> 00:22:04,030
Our goal should be for
the betterment of mankind,

526
00:22:04,030 --> 00:22:07,180
and then our hearts
and our land will mend.

527
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:08,290
♪

528
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:11,150
I couldn't have
said it better myself.

529
00:22:11,150 --> 00:22:13,100
Let us always be together,

530
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:14,270
in life

531
00:22:14,270 --> 00:22:16,150
as well as in spirit.

532
00:22:16,150 --> 00:22:38,230
♪

533
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:42,080
(theme song)

534
00:22:42,080 --> 00:25:03,060
♪

535
00:25:04,090 --> 00:25:07,020
♪

